Turnbull and Bishop characters rap on Open Slather Cast of Comedy Central show Open Slather impersonate Malcolm Turnbull and Julie Bishop performing their own rendition of Macklemore and Ryan Lewis track Downtown .
PT0M52S http://www.canberratimes.com.au/action/externalEmbeddedPlayer?id=d-43rxl 620 349 October 2, 2015 - 1:30PM Autoplay On Off Video feedback Video settings "His name's Malcolm – notable genius – and he's gathering the numbers with Arthur Sinodinos ... " 
Meet prime minister Malcolm Turnbull as you've (hopefully) never imagined him before – as a rap star in a parody of Macklemore's Downtown .
Played by Dave Eastgate with Jane Turner (Kath of Kath & Kim  fame) perfecting her best laser death stare as Julie Bishop, Turnbull sweeps all before him as he snatches the leadership from a Speedo-clad Tony Abbott (Jay K Cagatay).
Malcolm-more ... Dave Eastgate as Malcolm Turnbull. 
There's even a brief reference to Macklemore's Thrift Shop with "Malcolm-more" strutting his stuff in an outsize fur coat.
Advertisement And while it won't exactly pass for serious political commentary, it's all good fun from Comedy Central's Open Slather team.
It might even inspire Turnbull to bust a few moves in the House of Reps. It'd certainly liven up Prime Minister's Questions and who could resist the idea of Christopher Pyne and Julie Bishop throwing a few shapes on the front bench?
